	will be on by default. Edits so the example will work with old sh
	implementations. 

	* common_tests.exp: Two changes/fixes: The char-by-char break down
	of how comp and expected output differ is printed on if $verbose
	is >= 3. Also, the second 'fail ...' call has been removed. this
	caused tests to FAIL with $verbose was >=1 even though they really
	passed. 

	* aclocal.m4: Modified the test for librx so it's effectively not
	used. The regex code is now included in libdap++. Fixed a bug in
	the DODS_MAT macro. 

	* FilterDirHTML.pm: Fixed bug 702: HREFed URLs in the return
	document were not quoted. This code worked with most browsers but
	failed for some HTML parsers.

	* Added HTTP response status line and Content-Type header for the
	directory response to DODS_Dispatch.pm.

